      "content": "look i've tried the doctor thing and they just say everything is \"normal.\" but it doesn't feel normal. think about it—these trading algos operate on millisecond timescales using massive amounts of electrical energy/EM signatures. if my nervous system is sensitive enough, couldn't there be a resonance between the rapid fluctuations in market data and my own bio-electrical signals? it feels less like \"seeing the future\" and more like my body is just picking up on the literal energy of the trade executions before they are even fully processed by the retail exchange. isn't it possible that \"mainstream science\" just hasn't looked at the intersection of bio-electromagnetics and high-frequency finance yet?",
